# Mutation Feedback (MANDATORY)

Every operation that **creates, updates, or deletes** data must show toast feedback on both **success** and **error**. No silent mutations.

## How

1. Import `toast` from `sonner`.
2. Wire toasts at the **call site** (inside the submit handler or mutation callback), not deep inside utility functions.
3. Show a `toast.success` on success and a `toast.error` on failure — both are required.

## Standard Pattern

```typescript
// GOOD — both outcomes covered
import { toast } from 'sonner';

async function handleSave(data: FormValues) {
  try {
    await saveProperty(data);
    toast.success('Propiedad guardada correctamente');
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('[Save Property Error]:', error);
    toast.error('Error al guardar la propiedad');
  }
}
```

## With Loading State

```typescript
const [isSaving, setIsSaving] = useState(false);

async function handleSave(data: FormValues) {
  setIsSaving(true);
  try {
    await saveProperty(data);
    toast.success('Propiedad guardada correctamente');
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('[Save Property Error]:', error);
    toast.error('Error al guardar la propiedad');
  } finally {
    setIsSaving(false);
  }
}

<Button disabled={isSaving}>
  {isSaving ? 'Guardando…' : 'Guardar'}
</Button>
```

## With Backend Error Message

When the Supabase or API error includes a useful message, surface it in the toast description:

```typescript
} catch (error) {
  const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : undefined;
  console.error('[Save Property Error]:', error);
  toast.error('Error al guardar la propiedad', {
    description: message,
  });
}
```

## Supabase Pattern

Supabase returns `{ data, error }` — check the error before assuming success:

```typescript
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from('properties')
  .update(payload)
  .eq('id', id);

if (error) {
  console.error('[Update Property Error]:', error);
  toast.error('Error al actualizar la propiedad', { description: error.message });
  return;
}

toast.success('Propiedad actualizada');
```

## Rules

- `toast.error` must always include a `title`. Include a `description` when a backend error message is available.
- `toast.success` must always include a `title`. A `description` is optional.
- Never use `alert()`, `window.confirm()`, `console.log`, or inline text banners as substitutes for toast feedback.
- Never show a success toast if the operation may have failed (always check `error` from Supabase before toasting success).

## What Counts as a Mutation

Any of: Supabase `.insert()`, `.update()`, `.upsert()`, `.delete()`, API route `POST/PATCH/PUT/DELETE`, file upload/delete, or any function that persists data.

Read-only operations (`SELECT`, `.select()`, GET requests) do **not** require success toasts, but must still handle and toast errors.
